items.name: Object_UIElement
items.content: # =================================================================== # # Script: Object_UIElement # # $$COPYRIGHT$$ # # =================================================================== class Object_UIElement extends gs.Object_Base # # The UI object's image used for visual presentation. # @property image # @type string # @accessors "image", set: (image) -> if image != @image_ @image_ = image @needsUpdate = yes get: -> @image_ # # The UI object's image used for visual presentation. # @property image # @type string # @accessors "opacity", set: (opacity) -> if opacity != @opacity_ @opacity_ = opacity @needsUpdate = yes get: -> @opacity_ # # The UI object's image used for visual presentation. # @property image # @type string # @accessors "clipRect", set: (clipRect) -> if clipRect != @clipRect_ @clipRect_ = clipRect @needsUpdate = yes get: -> @clipRect_ @accessors "visible", set: (v) -> if v != @visible_ @visible_ = v @needsUpdate = yes @fullRefresh() get: -> @visible_ and (!@parent or @parent.visible) ###* * The base class for all In-Game UI objects. * * @module ui * @class Object_UIElement * @extends gs.Object_Base * @memberof ui * @constructor ### constructor: -> super() @id = "" ###* * Indicates if that UI object will break the binding-chain. If true the UI object * will not change any binding-targets for the current binding-execution period. * @property breakBindingChain * @type boolean ### @breakBindingChain = no @numbers = new Array(10) @data = new Array(10) @controlsByStyle = new Array(ui.UIManager.stylesById.length) @parentsByStyle = new Array(ui.UIManager.stylesById.length) @styles = [] @activeStyles = [] @focusable = no ###* * The UI object's destination rectangle on screen. * @property dstRect * @type ui.Component_UIElementRectangle ### @dstRect = new ui.UIElementRectangle(this) ###* * The UI object's margin. The margin defines an extra space around the UI object. * The default is { left: 0, top: 0, right: 0, bottom: 0 }. * @property margin * @type ui.Space ### @margin = new ui.Space(0, 0, 0, 0) ###* * The UI object's padding. The default is { left: 0, top: 0, right: 0, bottom: 0 }. * @property padding * @type ui.Space ### @padding = new ui.Space(0, 0, 0, 0) ###* * The UI object's alignment. * @property alignment * @type ui.Alignment ### @alignment = 0 ###* * Indicates if the UI object is visible on screen. * @property visible * @type boolean ### @visible = yes ###* * Indicates if the UI object is enabled and responds to user actions. * @property enabled * @type boolean ### @enabled = yes ###* * The UI object's origin. * @property origin * @type gs.Vector2 ### @origin = new ui.UIElementPoint(this) #x: 0, y: 0 ###* * The UI object's offset. * @property offset * @type gs.Vector2 ### @offset = new ui.UIElementPoint(this) #x: 0, y: 0 ###* * The UI object's opacity to control transparency. For example: 0 = Transparent, 255 = Opaque, 128 = Semi-Transparent. * @property opacity * @type number ### @opacity = 255 ###* * The UI object's resize behavior. * @property resizable * @type boolean ### @resizable = no ###* * The UI object's anchor-point. For example: An anchor-point with 0,0 places the object with its top-left corner * at its position but with an 0.5, 0.5 anchor-point the object is placed with its center. An anchor-point of 1,1 * places the object with its lower-right corner. * @property anchor * @type gs.Point ### @anchor = new gs.Point(0.0, 0.0) ###* * The UI object's zoom-setting for x and y axis. The default value is * { x: 1.0, y: 1.0 } * @property zoom * @type gs.Point ### @zoom = new gs.Point(1.0, 1.0) ###* * The UI object's color. * @property color * @type gs.Color ### @color = new Color(255, 255, 255, 0) @tone = new Tone(0, 0, 0, 0) ###* * The UI object's rotation-angle in degrees. The rotation center depends on the * anchor-point. * @property angle * @type number ### @angle = 0 ###* * The UI object's mask for masking-effects. * @property mask * @type gs.Mask ### @mask = new gs.Mask() ###* * An event-emitter to emit events. * @property events * @type gs.Component_EventEmitter ### @events = new gs.EventEmitter() ###* * The update-behavior of the UI object. The default is ui.UpdateBehavior.NORMAL. * @property updateBehavior * @type ui.UpdateBehavior ### @updateBehavior = ui.UpdateBehavior.NORMAL ###* * @property image_ * @type string * @protected ### @image_ = null ###* * The object's clip-rect for visual presentation. * @property clipRect_ * @type gs.Rect * @protected ### @clipRect_ = null ###* * @property visible_ * @type boolean * @protected ### @visible_ = yes @addComponent(@events) ###* * Restores the object from a data-bundle. * * @method restore * @param {Object} data - The data-bundle. ### restore: (data) -> @anchor = new gs.Point(data.anchor.x, data.anchor.y) @offset = new gs.Point(data.offset.x, data.offset.y) @dstRect.x = data.x @dstRect.y = data.y @opacity = data.opacity @zoom = new gs.Point(data.zoom.x, data.zoom.y) @angle = data.angle @zIndex = data.zIndex @visible_ = data.visible @rid = data.rid ###* * Serializes the object into a data-bundle. * * @method toDataBundle * @return {Object} The data-bundle. ### toDataBundle: -> return { rid: @rid, x: @dstRect.x, y: @dstRect.y, opacity: @opacity, zoom: @zoom, angle: @angle, anchor: { x: @anchor.x, y: @anchor.y }, zIndex: @zIndex, offset: { x: @offset.x, y: @offset.y }, visible: @visible_ } ui.Object_UIElement = Object_UIElement
